class.name: Attr
class.description: The Attr interface represents an attribute in an Element object.

class.name: CharacterData
class.description: This interface represents a block of XML character data.

method.name: __new__
method.abstract: T.__new__(S, ...) -> a new object with type S, a subtype of T

method.name: __repr__
method.abstract: x.__repr__() <==> repr(x)

method.name: appendData
method.abstract: Append the string to the end of the character data of the node.

method.name: deleteData
method.abstract: Remove a range of unicode units from the node.

method.name: insertData
method.abstract: Insert a string at the specified unicode unit offset.

method.name: replaceData
method.abstract: Replace the characters starting at the specified unicode unit offset with the specified string.

method.name: substringData
method.abstract: Extracts a range of data from the node.

class.name: Comment
class.description: This interface represents the content of a comment, i.e., all the characters between the starting '<!--' and ending '-->'.

class.name: DOMImplementation
class.abstract: The DOMImplementation interface provides a number of methods for performing operations that are independent of any particular instance of the document object model.

method.name: __repr__
method.abstract: x.__repr__() <==> repr(x)

method.name: createDocument
method.abstract: Creates a Document object of the specified type with its document element.

method.name: createRootNode
method.abstract: Creates a Document object with the specified documentURI.

method.name: hasFeature
method.abstract: Test if the DOM implementation implements a specific feature.

class.name: Document
class.description: The Document interface represents the entire XML document. Conceptually, it is the root of the document tree, and provides the primary access to the document's data.

method.name: __new__
method.abstract: T.__new__(S, ...) -> a new object with type S, a subtype of T

method.name: __repr__
method.abstract: x.__repr__() <==> repr(x)

method.name: createAttributeNS
method.abstract: createAttributeNS(namespaceURI, qualifiedName) -> new Attribute
method.description: Creates an attribute of the given qualified name and namespace URI.

method.name: createComment
method.abstract: createComment(data) -> new Comment
method.description: Creates a Comment node given the specified string.

method.name: createDocumentFragment
method.abstract: createDocumentFragment() -> new DocumentFragment

method.name: createElementNS
method.abstract: createElementNS(namespaceURI, qualifiedName) -> new Element
method.description: Creates an element of the given qualified name and namespace URI.

method.name: createProcessingInstruction
method.abstract: createProcessingInstruction(target, data) -> new ProcessingInstruction
method.description: Creates a ProcessingInstruction node given the specified name and data strings.

method.name: createTextNode
method.abstract: createTextNode(data) -> new Text
method.description: Creates a Text node given the specified string.

method.name: getElementById
method.abstract: getElementById(elementId) -> Element
method.description: Returns the Element whose ID is given by elementId. If no such element exists, returns None. If more than one element has this ID, the first in the document is returned.

method.name: importNode
method.abstract: importNode(importedNode, deep) -> Node
method.description: Imports a node from another document to this document. The returned node has no parent; (parentNode is None). The source node is not altered or removed from the original document; this method creates a new copy of the source node.

class.name: DocumentFragment
class.description: DocumentFragment is a "lightweight" or "minimal" Document object.

method.name: __new__
method.abstract: T.__new__(S, ...) -> a new object with type S, a subtype of T

method.name: __repr__
method.abstract: x.__repr__() <==> repr(x)

class.name: Element
class.description: The Element interface represents an element in an XML document.

method.name: __new__
method.abstract: T.__new__(S, ...) -> a new object with type S, a subtype of T

method.name: __repr__
method.abstract: x.__repr__() <==> repr(x)

method.name: getAttributeNS
method.abstract: Retrieves an attribute value by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: getAttributeNodeNS
method.abstract: Retrieves an Attr node by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: hasAttributeNS
method.abstract: Returns True when an attribute with a given local name and namespace URI is specified on this element or has a default value, False otherwise.

method.name: removeAttributeNS
method.abstract: Removes an attribute by local name and namespace URI.

method.name: removeAttributeNode
method.abstract: Removes the specified attribute node.

method.name: setAttributeNS
method.abstract: Adds a new attribute. If an attribute with the same local name and namespace URI is already present on the element, its prefix is changed to be the prefix part of the qualifiedName, and its value is changed to be the value parameter.

method.name: setAttributeNodeNS
method.abstract: Adds a new attribute. If an attribute with that local name and that namespace URI is already present in the element, it is replaced by the new one. Replacing an attribute node by itself has no effect.

class.name: Node
class.abstract: The Node type is the primary datatype for the entire Document Object Model.

method.name: __hash__
method.abstract: x.__hash__() <==> hash(x)

method.name: __iter__
method.abstract: x.__iter__() <==> iter(x)

method.name: __repr__
method.abstract: x.__repr__() <==> repr(x)

method.name: appendChild
method.abstract: Adds the node newChild to the end of the list of children of this node.

method.name: cloneNode
method.abstract: Returns a duplicate of this node, i.e., serves as a generic copy constructor for nodes.

method.name: hasChildNodes
method.abstract: Returns whether this node has any children.

method.name: insertBefore
method.abstract: Inserts the node newChild before the existing child node refChild.

method.name: isSameNode
method.abstract: Returns whether this node is the same node as the given one. (DOM Level 3)

method.name: normalize
method.abstract: Puts all Text nodes in the full depth of the sub-tree underneath this Node, including attribute nodes, into a "normal" form where only structure (e.g., elements, comments, processing instructions, CDATA sections, and entity references) separates Text nodes, i.e., there are neither adjacent Text nodes nor empty Text nodes.

method.name: removeChild
method.abstract: Removes the child node indicated by oldChild from the list of children, and returns it.

method.name: replaceChild
method.abstract: Replaces the child node oldChild with newChild in the list of children, and returns the oldChild node.

method.name: xpath
method.abstract: Evaluates an XPath expression string using this node as context.

class.name: ProcessingInstruction
class.description: The ProcessingInstruction interface represents a "processing instruction", used in XML as a way to keep processor-specific information in the text of the document.

method.abstract: T.__new__(S, ...) -> a new object with type S, a subtype of T

method.name: __repr__
method.abstract: x.__repr__() <==> repr(x)

class.name: Text
class.description: This interface represents the contents of a text node.

class.name: XPathNamespace
class.description: The XPathNamespace interface represents the XPath namespace node type that DOM lacks.

method.name: __new__
method.abstract: T.__new__(S, ...) -> a new object with type S, a subtype of T

method.name: __repr__

function.name: GetAllNs
function.description: Get all of the namespaces defined in scope of this node.

function.name: ProcessFragment
function.abstract: Take an XPointer fragment and return a structure suitable for the cDomlette parser to update state tables Xptr e.g. xmlns(x=http://uche.ogbuji.net/eg) xpointer(/x:spam/x:eggs)

function.name: SeekNss
function.description: Traverses the tree to seek an approximate set of defined namespaces.
